          • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

            It's an easy game-plan for Stuttgart, stick everyone behind the ball and look to counter with pace. Easier said than done of course. It'll be a typical Bayern league home game and it depends how long Stuttgart can hold out. If it's 0-0 after 80 minutes then nerves will creep in and possibly mistakes, although they are rare at the Allianz in domestic games. Stuttgart just have to hope a bit of complacency sneaks into Bayern's game after the good win midweek which they can exploit- otherwise they don't stand a chance of getting even a point. For Bayern, I expect Robben to start. It's the type of game where he will be able to get into the swing of things slowly, have multiple early touches and "gentle" runs before launching into his trademark quick, mazy dribbles. I personally wouldn't start Lewandowski. There's no reason to. Even if Stuttgart happen to fluke a win, Bayern will still eventually win the league but there are no guarantees in the CL. I predict 3-0 Bayern, Robben MotM.
